article.headline: Arkansas St. 68, Tenn.-Martin 63
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Adrian Banks had a career-high 32 points to lead Arkansas State to a 68-63 win over Tennessee-Martin on Monday night. Arkansas State (3-3) took a 31-26 lead at the half, shooting 42.9 percent from the field compared to 32 percent for Tennessee-Martin (1-4). Banks hit four 3-pointers in the first half and was 6-of-8 for the night. Isaac Wells added 13 points and 10 rebounds. The Skyhawks pulled even several times in the second half and took a brief 54-53 lead on a pair of free throws by Spencer Harris with 5:19 left. But Banks hit another 3 to take the lead for good. Zerek Knight led the Skyhawks with 19 points and seven rebounds, followed by Will Lewis with 14 points and nine rebounds. The Indians were 48.9 percent for the night from the field, to the Skyhawks' 35.3 percent. Tennessee-Martin controlled the boards 39-28.
